summary: This is a search warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York authorizing the search of Jeffrey Epstein's residence at 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY. The warrant seeks evidence related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy, listing specific items including a binder labeled 'NI Girls', massage tables, and other paraphernalia.

persons.name: Barbara Moses
persons.context: Issued the search warrant for the premises at 9 East 71st Street, authorizing the search related to sex trafficking violations.

events.title: Issuance of Search Warrant for Epstein Residence
events.description: A federal search warrant was issued authorizing law enforcement to search Jeffrey Epstein's New York City residence at 9 East 71st Street for evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.

locations: 9 East 71st Street, New York, New York
keyFacts: The search warrant targets Jeffrey Epstein's residence at 9 East 71st Street in New York City for evidence of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.
Specific items to be seized include a binder labeled 'NI Girls', which is described as containing documents or communications regarding victims or potential victims.
Other items listed for seizure include taxidermied dogs, massage tables and paraphernalia, busts of female torsos, nude photos in the 'Massage Room', and sex toys.
The warrant was issued by Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses and had to be executed by May 7, 2019, with authorization for delayed notice to the property owner.
The legal violations cited are Title 18, U.S. Code, Sections 1591 (sex trafficking of minors) and 371 (conspiracy).
